{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e7377424-8e02-4810-83cd-6ed615179807","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively speaks the Microsoft.Testing.Platform protocol. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 opt-in bridge and is **no longer needed**. You can simply remove it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_014v428q2UVhnrcJWMhgNKBK","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01LmXy8NRn6mVvshwvvE1Wc6","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-63f482650eee41698cba929e9707a182/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-63f482650eee41698cba929e9707a182/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"e42cfa6e-9c81-408c-8a82-0d9924351a8c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) support. Let me provide accurate information.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` has native support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The key change is:\n\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP natively — the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed. It was a bridge property for .NET 9 to opt into MTP support with `dotnet test`.\n\n2. In .NET 10, MTP is the default test runner for `dotnet test`, so `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` can be removed.\n\n\nNow I'll show them how to update their project file to remove that property since it's no longer necessary.","outputTokens":445,"requestId":"A032:1619CB:D03559:F172A9:69FE877D"},"id":"70324593-4390-4fb5-aac7-db72c2f7326b","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:01:57.511Z","parentId":"38de71a7-94aa-4289-bbdd-fbae2952ec0d"}
